tatement fails, its changes are rolled back automatically and no further migrations in the same run are attempted.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real transactional behavior and stop-on-failure control flow must be validated across SQL execution, transaction wrapper, and migration loop modules. Unit tests with mocked transaction clients can miss rollback semantics. Rejected System because no real subprocess/OS primitive is required by the behavior text; a local Postgres integration test exercises the true failure boundary.","test_description":"Prepare migrations where one file performs a write then triggers SQL error, followed by another valid migration. Run runner against local test Postgres. Assert writes from failed migration are absent (rollback), later migration was not applied, and `_migrations` has no entry for failed/later versions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When two instances of the runner start at the same time against the same database, each migration is applied exactly once across both instances.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly depends on concurrent execution from 'two instances' (separate processes) plus DB locking/uniqueness under race. In-process fakes or single-process tests can miss inter-process timing and contention failures. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no AI/LLM step exists in the behavior.","test_description":"Launch two runner subprocesses simultaneously against the same Postgres instance and shared migrations directory. After both exit, assert each migration’s side effect appears exactly once and `_migrations` contains one row per version with no duplicates.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"On the very first run against a fresh database, the `_migrations` table is created before any migration file is applied.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This checks startup orchestration between metadata bootstrap and migration application using real DB state on an empty schema. A unit test of 'ensureTable()' alone can miss ordering bugs in runner flow. Rejected System because behavior does not require subprocesses or OS-level effects; local DB + filesystem integration is sufficient.","test_description":"Start with an empty Postgres schema and at least one migration file that would fail if `_migrations` bookkeeping is absent. Run runner once and assert `_migrations` exists and first migration is applied successfully, proving metadata table creation happened first.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
